# Jikan API Proxy Environment Variable Integration Plan

We will refactor the AnimOrg backend to load the Cloudflare Worker proxy base URL dynamically from an environment variable named `JIKAN_PROXY_URL`, providing falling back defaults for resilience.

## Proposed Changes

### Environment Configuration

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/.env.example)
- Expose `JIKAN_PROXY_URL` with a placeholder value or example pointing to the Cloudflare Worker URL.

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/.env)
- Append `JIKAN_PROXY_URL=https://animorg-proxy.itisnexora.workers.dev/v4` to the local environment configuration.

---

### App Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [constants.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/config/constants.ts)
- Load `BASE_URL` dynamically using `process.env.JIKAN_PROXY_URL`, defaulting to `https://animorg-proxy.itisnexora.workers.dev/v4` if undefined to ensure seamless execution.

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Manual Verification
- Compile and build the backend using `npm run build`.
- Verify local endpoints on local Node server.
- Commit, push, and monitor Render.
- Verify health check and proxy categories (e.g. home details page query).
